Yes, it seems like `addTable` returns an object containing the worksheet and table, instead of just the table:

```ts
  const table = sheet.addTable({
    name: st('entities.components'),
    ref: 'A2',
    columns: [
      { name: 'Label', filterButton: true },
      { name: nameColumnKey, filterButton: true },
    ],
    rows: [],
    headerRow: true,
    style: { theme: 'TableStyleLight1' },
  });

  console.log(table);
  ```

